{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.29",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 29,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 29",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 29 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:1",
      "text": "Job again took up his parable, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:2",
      "text": "“ Oh that I were as in the months of old, as in the days when God watched over me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:3",
      "text": "when his lamp shone on my head, and by his light I walked through darkness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:4",
      "text": "as I was in my prime, when the friendship of God was in my tent,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:5",
      "text": "when the Almighty was yet with me, and my children were around me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:6",
      "text": "when my steps were washed with butter, and the rock poured out streams of oil for me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:7",
      "text": "when I went out to the city gate, when I prepared my seat in the street.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:8",
      "text": "The young men saw me and hid themselves. The aged rose up and stood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:9",
      "text": "The princes refrained from talking, and laid their hand on their mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:10",
      "text": "The voice of the nobles was hushed, and their tongue stuck to the roof of their mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:11",
      "text": "For when the ear heard me, then it blessed me, and when the eye saw me, it commended me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:12",
      "text": "because I delivered the poor who cried, and the fatherless also, who had no one to help him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:13",
      "text": "the blessing of him who was ready to perish came on me, and I caused the widow’s heart to sing for joy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:14",
      "text": "I put on righteousness, and it clothed me. My justice was as a robe and a diadem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:15",
      "text": "I was eyes to the blind, and feet to the lame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:16",
      "text": "I was a father to the needy. I researched the cause of him whom I didn’t know.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:17",
      "text": "I broke the jaws of the unrighteous and plucked the prey out of his teeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:18",
      "text": "Then I said, ‘ I will die in my own house, I will count my days as the sand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:19",
      "text": "My root is spread out to the waters. The dew lies all night on my branch.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:20",
      "text": "My glory is fresh in me. My bow is renewed in my hand.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:21",
      "text": "“Men listened to me, waited, and kept silence for my counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:22",
      "text": "After my words they didn’t speak again. My speech fell on them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:23",
      "text": "They waited for me as for the rain. Their mouths drank as with the spring rain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:24",
      "text": "I smiled on them when they had no confidence. They didn’t reject the light of my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.29.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:25",
      "text": "I chose out their way, and sat as chief. I lived as a king in the army, as one who comforts the mourners.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
